{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ba0be387-bb47-4d3d-ac05-5c59f8cac9bd",
    "name": "API Gateway Auth Testing - API Key & JWT",
    "description": "Collection for testing Kong API Gateway with two authentication flows:\n\n## Authentication Flows\n\n### 1. API Key Flow (Service-to-Service)\n- Used for backend services, admin tools, or service accounts\n- Tenant credentials managed via Kong API key plugin\n- Simple header-based authentication\n\n### 2. JWT Flow (User/Frontend)\n- Used for end-user authentication (CSS SSO)\n- Browser frontend logs in via SSO → receives JWT\n- Frontend sends JWT with requests → Kong validates signature\n- Perfect for public apps with user authentication\n\n## Setup Instructions\n\n1. Run Kong seed script: `docker-compose up kong-migrations && docker-compose up kong`\n2. Choose authentication method below\n3. Run appropriate requests\n\n## Test Credentials\n\n**API Key Method:**\n- API Key: `test-api-key-a-12345678901234567890`\n\n**JWT Method:**\n- Key: `test-tenant-a`\n- Secret: `secret-key-for-tenant-a-do-not-use-in-production`\n- Use the \"Generate JWT\" request to create tokens\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "9083839"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "JWT Flow (User/Frontend Auth)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Generate JWT Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Generate a JWT token for testing",
                  "// This simulates a token issued by CSS SSO",
                  "",
                  "const crypto = require('crypto');",
                  "",
                  "function base64UrlEncode(str) {",
                  "    return Buffer.from(str, 'utf8')",
                  "        .toString('base64')",
                  "        .replace(/\\+/g, '-')",
                  "        .replace(/\\//g, '_')",
                  "        .replace(/=/g, '');",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "// JWT Header",
                  "const header = {",
                  "    'alg': 'HS256',",
                  "    'typ': 'JWT',",
                  "    'kid': 'test-tenant-a'  // Key ID matching Kong consumer",
                  "};",
                  "",
                  "// JWT Payload (customize as needed)",
                  "const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);",
                  "const payload = {",
                  "    'iss': 'test-tenant-a',              // Issuer (matches Kong JWT key)",
                  "    'sub': 'user-123',                    // Subject (user ID)",
                  "    'iat': now,                           // Issued at",
                  "    'exp': now + 3600,                    // Expires in 1 hour",
                  "    'aud': 'notify-api',                  // Audience",
                  "    'tenant_id': 'tenant-a',              // Custom claim: tenant",
                  "    'user_id': 'user-123',                // Custom claim: user",
                  "    'email': 'user@example.com'           // Custom claim: email",
                  "};",
                  "",
                  "// Encode header and payload",
                  "const encodedHeader = base64UrlEncode(JSON.stringify(header));",
                  "const encodedPayload = base64UrlEncode(JSON.stringify(payload));",
                  "const message = encodedHeader + '.' + encodedPayload;",
                  "",
                  "// Create signature using JWT secret",
                  "const jwtSecret = pm.environment.get('JWT_SECRET_A');",
                  "const signature = crypto",
                  "    .createHmac('sha256', jwtSecret)",
                  "    .update(message)",
                  "    .digest('base64')",
                  "    .replace(/\\+/g, '-')",
                  "    .replace(/\\//g, '_')",
                  "    .replace(/=/g, '');",
                  "",
                  "// Combine all parts",
                  "const jwt = message + '.' + signature;",
                  "",
                  "// Save to environment",
                  "pm.environment.set('jwt_token', jwt);",
                  "pm.environment.set('jwt_payload', JSON.stringify(payload, null, 2));",
                  "",
                  "console.log('JWT Generated:');",
                  "console.log('Token:', jwt);",
                  "console.log('Payload:', payload);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('JWT Token Generated', function () {",
                  "    const jwt = pm.environment.get('jwt_token');",
                  "    pm.expect(jwt).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(jwt.split('.').length).to.equal(3);  // Valid JWT format",
                  "    ",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://httpbin.org/get",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["httpbin", "org"],
              "path": ["get"]
            },
            "description": "This is a helper request that generates a JWT token using HMAC-SHA256.\n\nThe token simulates a JWT issued by CSS SSO with custom claims for your application.\n\n**Token Claims:**\n- `iss`: Issuer (matches Kong consumer key)\n- `sub`: Subject (user ID)\n- `iat`: Issued at timestamp\n- `exp`: Expiration (1 hour)\n- `tenant_id`: Your custom claim\n- `user_id`: Your custom claim\n- `email`: Your custom claim\n\nThe generated JWT is stored in the environment variable `{{jwt_token}}`"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Tenant (JWT)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201 || pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (jsonData.apiKey) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('generated_api_key', jsonData.apiKey);",
                  "        pm.test('Tenant created - API Key saved', function() {",
                  "            pm.expect(jsonData.apiKey).to.exist;",
                  "            pm.expect(jsonData.tenant).to.exist;",
                  "            pm.expect(jsonData.tenant.id).to.exist;",
                  "        });",
                  "        console.log('✅ Tenant created successfully!');",
                  "        console.log('Tenant ID:', jsonData.tenant.id);",
                  "        console.log('API Key:', jsonData.apiKey);",
                  "    }",
                  "} else {",
                  "    pm.test('Failed to create tenant', function() {",
                  "        pm.expect.fail('Tenant creation failed: ' + pm.response.status);",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{oauth_access_token}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"my-test-tenant\",\n  \"description\": \"Test tenant for API development\",\n  \"organization\": \"BC Government\",\n  \"contactEmail\": \"admin@bcgov.ca\",\n  \"contactName\": \"Admin User\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kong_url}}/api/v1/admin/tenants",
              "host": ["{{kong_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "admin", "tenants"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new tenant and get an API key.\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n1. Run \"Get OAuth Token from CSS SSO\" first to get `{{oauth_access_token}}`\n2. Or use \"Generate JWT Token\" for local testing\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"tenant\": {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"name\": \"my-test-tenant\",\n    \"status\": \"active\"\n  },\n  \"apiKey\": \"generated-api-key-value\",\n  \"note\": \"Store this key securely\"\n}\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- The API key is shown only once - save it!\n- The generated API key is automatically saved to `{{generated_api_key}}` environment variable\n- Use this key for subsequent API Key Flow requests"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Health Check (JWT)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{oauth_access_token}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kong_url}}/api/health",
              "host": ["{{kong_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Test health endpoint with JWT authentication from CSS SSO.\n\nUse either:\n1. **`{{oauth_access_token}}`** - Real token from \"Get OAuth Token from CSS SSO\"\n2. **`{{jwt_token}}`** - Local test token from \"Generate JWT Token\" (dev only)\n\nKong validates:\n1. JWT signature is correct\n2. Token has not expired\n3. Issuer (`iss`) matches a registered consumer\n\nThe request is forwarded to the backend with user information in headers."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Tenants (JWT)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{oauth_access_token}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kong_url}}/api/v1/admin/tenants",
              "host": ["{{kong_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "admin", "tenants"]
            },
            "description": "Get all tenants using JWT authentication from CSS SSO.\n\nUse either:\n1. **`{{oauth_access_token}}`** - Real token from \"Get OAuth Token from CSS SSO\"\n2. **`{{jwt_token}}`** - Local test token from \"Generate JWT Token\" (dev only)\n\nKong extracts user claims from JWT and may pass them as headers:\n- `X-Consumer-ID`: Kong consumer ID\n- `X-Consumer-Username`: Consumer username\n- `X-Authenticated-Userid`: Authenticated user ID"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
